I had disappeared behind some remote dove-gray horizon while my former compatriots are still sipping cranberry drinks at a seaside stall.





Yours,

Vladimir Nabokov2





TO: JAMES HARRIS1

CC, 1 p.





Brockway Hotel

Brockway, California

August 12, 1959

